{
  "texts": [
    "The test results are informative and can be used while building a navigation system for visually impaired individuals [1,4].",
    "Two primary metrics were utilized to gauge the models' detection performance:1) Intersection over Union (IoU): Measures overlap between predicted and ground-truth bounding boxes.",
    "IoU is computed as:IoU = Area of Overlap Area of UnionUsed for evaluating localization accuracy in object detection [3,7].",
    "2) Mean Average Precision (mAP): Aggregated measure of precision across IoU thresholds.",
    "Average Precision (AP) at a specific IoU threshold:AP = TP TP + FPmAP is the mean of AP values across recall levels and is a standard metric in object detection [3,7].TABLE II: Validation Accuracy Model Dataset Metrics Avg."
  ]
}